Be brave. Anything you want to do you can do here. You can create beautiful things - but you have to see them in your mind first. Trees get lonely too, so we'll give him a little friend. If there's two big trees invariably sooner or later there's gonna be a little tree.

Do an almighty painting with us. We spend so much of our life looking - but never seeing. Let's do that again. We touch the canvas, the canvas takes what it wants. You can work and carry-on and put lots of little happy things in here.

Just think about these things in your mind and drop em' on canvas. Let all these little things happen. Don't fight them. Learn to use them. Didn't you know you had that much power? You can move mountains. You can do anything. That is when you can experience true joy, when you have no fear.
